15/12/2008
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Martin Dimitrov, one of six candidates to be leader of the Union of Democratic Forces (UDF), Bulgaria's strongest right-wing party, is leading party elections, according to preliminary figures released on Sunday (December 14th).
This marked the first time a UDF leader was elected through a popular vote among all party members.
Turnout was more than 75%.
Dimitrov, 31, is an economist and parliament member.
If elected, he will be the youngest leader of a major political party.
(Dnevnik - 15/12/08;
Sofia news agency, Darik - 14/12/08)
